Cars.co.za has named the finalists of its 2019/20 consumer awards. The finalists were selected out of 65 vehicles that Cars.co.za’s extended editorial team agreed were the best derivatives available in the South African new passenger vehicle market as of 1 September 2019. 17 brands are represented in the list of finalists, with Volkswagen leading the nominations with 7 derivatives, followed by BMW, Ford and Toyota (4 car), Mazda and Suzuki (3 cars). Chinese SUV brand Haval also made its first appearance, while Jaguar and Land Rover return to the list after failing to make the last round in 2018/19. The finalists in their respective categories are as follows: Budget Car  Kia Picanto 1.2 Style
